The paper deals with interactive coding over imperfect channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The focus on workload balancing and passing coordination duties suggests a distributed computing (cs.DC) aspect to the work. The use of protocols and mechanisms also suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
